						               													<description>Los Tres Reinos (AKA Ajetrez), is an innovative strategy game for three players, developed in Venezuela.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Actually, more than a game, it is a story of medieval fantasy, in which three kingdoms require solving the situation that is presented to them by having grown to the point that their populations have begun to mix. The Monarchs of these kingdoms come together to resolve this situation, leading them to make a strategy game that shows who is the right leader to lead these realms as one, this  story takes us to an exciting board game were will be revealed who is the most appropriate leader to rule the destiny of the resulting kingdom.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The desired thing is to reunite the families around a fun board game and develop their intellect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The main objective of the game it&amp;acute;s to conquer the other 2 kingdoms, by strategy and negotiation keeping the balance among the powers, the winner it&amp;acute;s the player that captures the leaders of the other kingdoms.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This boardgame reimplements chess into a 3 players game,where the classic chess rules were modified to make a balanced 3 way game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes a circular grid board, 57 pieces among 3 kingdoms colors (red, white, Black) rules, storybook and scoring Sheets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game it&amp;acute;s intended for competitive scene with tournaments and leagues.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
